 then gently spread ¼ prepared sushi rice over nori sheet with a wet, soft spatula (see tip), leaving ⅓ clear at far end. Sprinkle ½ Tbsp toasted sesame seeds over rice then, very carefully, flip nori sheet over so that it is rice side down on mat and the clear end is nearest to you. Spread ½ Tbsp mascarpone in a line across base of nori sheet 1 cm from the edge. Top with a line of avocado slices, cucumber matchsticks and leaves from 2 sprigs coriander."},{"content":"Using bamboo sushi mat, begin rolling tightly to form a roll. Before reaching the other end brush edge of nori vinegar-water (see tip) to help seal, then continue rolling tightly. Set roll aside then continue assembling remaining rolls."},{"content":"Lightly spread mascarpone cheese on smoked salmon pieces then lay on sushi rolls. Trim any smoked salmon overhanging at the sides."},{"content":"Slice each roll into 1.5 cm pieces using a wet, sharp knife and serve with reserved soy and wasabi dipping sauce."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Many people think sushi means raw fish, but it is actually a reference to vinegared rice combined with various ingredients.","Place <b>200 g<b> water and <b>2 Tbsp<b> rice vinegar in a bowl to use for brushing and keeping hands and utensils wet so they don't stick to the rice.","Traditionally sushi rice should be body temperature rather than chilled, therefore for optimum quality, sushi is best served immediately or within a few hours of making. Wrap rolls in cling film and leave in a cool dry place then slice just before serving.","Sushi can be wrapped in cling film and refrigerated. Consume within 24 hours but be mindful that the quality decreases quickly due to the rice losing moisture."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 20m","36 pieces"]}